quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,Have We not expanded your chest
  94,2,And removed from you your burden
  94,3,Which galled your back
  94,4,And raised high the esteem you are held
  94,5,"So indeed, with every difficulty there is relief"
  94,6,"Indeed, with every difficulty there is relief"
  94,7,"Therefore, when you are free, still labor hard"
  94,8,And turn all of your attention to your Lord
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,And Mount Sinai
  95,3,And this city of security
  95,4,We have indeed created the human being in the best of forms
  95,5,Then We debase them to the lowest of the low
  95,6,"Except those who believe and do righteous deeds, for they will have a reward unfailing"
  95,7,"Then what can, after this, deceive you about the judgment"
  95,8,Is not God the Wisest of Judges
  96,1,"Read, in the name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,Created the human being from a zygote
  96,3,"Proclaim, and your Lord is Most Bountiful"
  96,4,He Who taught the use of the pen
  96,5,Taught the human being that which he knew not
  96,6,"No, but the human being transgresses all bounds"
  96,7,When he looks upon himself as self-sufficient
  96,8,"Indeed, to your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Do you see one who forbids
  96,10,A worshipper when he turns to pray
  96,11,Have you seen whether he has guidance
  96,12,Or encourages righteousness
  96,13,Do you see if he denies and turns away
  96,14,Does he not know that God sees
  96,15,"Let him beware, that if he does not desist, We will drag him by the hair of his head"
  96,16,"His lying, sinful head"
  96,17,Then let him call to his advisers
  96,18,We will call on the angels of punishment
  96,19,"No, do not follow, but bow down in adoration, and bring yourself ever closer"
  97,1,We have indeed revealed it in the Night of Power
  97,2,And what will explain to you what the Night of Power is
  97,3,The Night of Power is as good as a thousand months
  97,4,"There comes down the angels and the spirit by God's permission, for every will"
  97,5,"Peace, until the rise of morn"
  98,1,Those who reject it among the people of the Book and among the polytheists were not going to depart until there came to them clear evidence
  98,2,"A messenger from God, rehearsing scriptures kept pure"
  98,3,"In it are laws, right and straight"
  98,4,"Nor did the people of the Book form sects, until after there came to them clear evidence"
  98,5,"And they have been asked no more than this— to worship God, offer Him sincere devotion, be truthful, establish prayer, and give zakat, and that is the way of life which is right and straight"
  98,6,"Those who reject it among the people of the Book and among the polytheists, will be in hellfire, to dwell therein forever. They are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,"Those who have faith and do righteous deeds, they are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with God is gardens of eternity, beneath which rivers flow, they will dwell therein forever, God well pleased with them, and they with Him. All this for those who are conscious of their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken to its utmost convulsion
  99,2,And the earth throws up its burden
  99,3,"And the human being yells, “What is the matter with it?”"
  99,4,On that day it will declare its information
  99,5,Because your Lord would have given it inspiration
  99,6,"On that day, humanity will proceed in groups sorted out, to be shown their deeds"
  99,7,Then anyone who has done an atom’s weight of good see it
  99,8,And anyone who has done an atom’s weight of wrong will see it
  100,1,By those who race with panting breath
  100,2,And strike sparks of fire
  100,3,And push home the charge in the morning
  100,4,And raise the dust in clouds
  100,5,And move forward en masse
  100,6,Truly the human being is ungrateful to their Guardian Evolver
  100,7,And to that they bear witness
  100,8,And violent is their love of wealth